### Step-by-Step Guide to Configure Resilience in Flink Jobs

#### 1. **Flink Job Configuration**
Ensure your Flink jobs use a fixed delay restart strategy with three retries and a ten-second delay between retries.

#### Example Flink Job Setup
```java
import org.apache.flink.api.common.restartstrategy.RestartStrategies;
import org.apache.flink.streaming.api.CheckpointingMode;
import org.apache.flink.streaming.api.TimeCharacteristic;
import org.apache.flink.streaming.api.environment.StreamExecutionEnvironment;

public class OrderProcessingJob {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        final StreamExecutionEnvironment env = StreamExecutionEnvironment.getExecutionEnvironment();

        // Set checkpointing mode
        env.enableCheckpointing(5000, CheckpointingMode.EXACTLY_ONCE);

        // Set time characteristic to event-time processing
        env.setStreamTimeCharacteristic(TimeCharacteristic.EventTime);

        // Configure fixed delay restart strategy with 3 retries and 10-second delay between retries
        env.getConfig().setRestartStrategy(RestartStrategies.fixedDelayRestart(3, Time.seconds(10)));

        // Add your Flink job logic here

        env.execute("Order Processing Job");
    }
}
```

