### State Recovery Expectations

#### 1. **Checkpointing**
Flink uses checkpointing to periodically save the current state of the streaming application. Checkpoints are used for fault tolerance and state recovery.

##### Configuration
- Enable checkpointing with `EXACTLY_ONCE` semantics.
- Set a reasonable interval between checkpoints (e.g., every 5 seconds).

```java
import org.apache.flink.streaming.api.CheckpointingMode;

public class FlinkJobConfig {

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
        final StreamExecutionEnvironment env = StreamExecutionEnvironment.getExecutionEnvironment();

        // Enable checkpointing with EXACTLY_ONCE semantics
        env.enableCheckpointing(5000, CheckpointingMode.EXACTLY_ONCE);

        // Set time characteristic to event-time processing
        env.setStreamTimeCharacteristic(TimeCharacteristic.EventTime);

        // Configure fixed delay restart strategy with 3 retries and 10-second delay between retries
        env.getConfig().setRestartStrategy(RestartStrategies.fixedDelayRestart(3, Time.seconds(10)));

        FlinkKafkaConsumer<String> kafkaConsumer = new FlinkKafkaConsumer<>(
                "order-topic",
                new SimpleStringSchema(),
                getProperties()
        );

        DataStream<OrderEvent> orderEvents = env.addSource(kafkaConsumer)
                                                 .map(new OrderEventDeserializer())
                                                 .assignTimestampsAndWatermarks(new OrderEventAssigner());

        // Apply window operations (e.g., tumbling windows)
        DataStream<AggregatedOrderData> aggregatedOrders = orderEvents
            .keyBy(order -> order.getOrderId())
            .timeWindow(Time.minutes(5))
            .reduce((order1, order2) -> {
                return new AggregatedOrderData(order1.getOrderTotal() + order2.getOrderTotal());
            });

        // Output the results to another Kafka topic or sink to a database
        aggregatedOrders.addSink(new FlinkKafkaProducer<>("aggregated-orders", new SimpleStringSchema(), getProperties()));

        // Execute the Flink job
        env.execute("Order Processing Job");
    }

    private static Properties getProperties() {
        Properties props = new Properties();
        props.setProperty("bootstrap.servers", "localhost:9092");
        props.setProperty("group.id", "flink-consumer-group");
        return props;
    }
}
```

